<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,258,1327]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1194,1219]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[365,444,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[172,1411,209,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[153,1433,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 11. Distribution of the central Andean Nepticulidae. 9, species recorded at altitudes below 3700 m; 10, 11, some collecting areas in Peru. * — Stigmella epicosma Meyrick is also known from Arica Province, northern Chile (Vargas 2011); ** – S. inca sp. nov. is also discovered in southern Ecuador." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/557158/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[461,536,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1922,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,208,1900]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1901]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 18. Distribution of some central Andean Nepticulidae. 12 – 14, 17, 18, habitats, Peru; 15, 16, distribution maps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/557159/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">14–16</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in the Peruvian Andes (
<collectingCountry box="[1086,1143,1195,1219]" name="Peru" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Peru</collectingCountry>
