<quantity box="[322,410,1231,1255]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.02" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="3020.0">3020 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,258,1327]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1266,1291]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<emphasis box="[810,891,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">lepidus</emphasis>
(nice, pretty) in reference to the bright, golden cream forewings irregularly speckled black-brown scales.
</paragraph>
